# budget.sheet — a small grocery budget.
# One line per row; commas separate columns; '#' lines are ignored.
# Commas inside parentheses belong to the formula, not the file format.
Item,Qty,Price,Total
Apples,4,1.50,=B2*C2
Bread,2,3.25,=B3*C3
Cheese,1,7.90,=B4*C4
Milk,3,0.95,=B5*C5
,,Subtotal,=sum(D2:D5)
,,Tax (8%),=D6*0.08
,,Total,=D6+D7
,,Priciest,=max(D2:D5)
,,Avg price,=avg(C2:C5)
